      "content": "but \"finding purpose\" requires someone to actually be there to experience it. if there's no one behind the mask, then there's no one to experience the help or the purpose. it's like trying to fix a house that's actually just an empty shell of a building. if the core is gone, the structure doesn't even matter anymore, right? it just feels like a hollow, endless cycle of pretending to be alive.",
